      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The expansion of welfare programs has had a complex impact on labor participation, often creating a disincentive for some individuals to seek full-time employment. Generous benefits can sometimes lead to a \"welfare trap,\" where the marginal benefit of working is outweighed by the potential loss of aid. However, proponents argue these programs provide a necessary economic floor, allowing people to pursue education or better job opportunities. Ultimately, the effect depends heavily on the specific design and phase-out rules of each program.",
